						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in a field near the river in the village.</p>						

						<p>Dēvarāya II, 1431 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1354, Virōdhikṛit, Bhādrapada ba. 1, Friday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1431 A.D., August 24.</hi> The Śaka year was current.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land, the details of which cannot be made out. It states that <hi rend="bold">Chandarasa-oḍeya</hi> who governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya</hi> and refers to a locality called Chōḷiya-kēri and to Śaṅkaradēva-oḍeya.</p>						

						</summary>
